Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. _____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION recognizing the
2 Donated Dental Services program.
3 Whereas, Recognizing a need for many Hoosiers, the
4 Indiana Dental Association and Dental Lifeline Network
5 teamed up to create Indiana's Donated Dental Services (DDS)
6 program;
7 Whereas, The DDS's goal is to help provide dental
8 treatment to Hoosiers who have disabilities, medical fragilities,
9 or are elderly;
10 Whereas, The DDS network includes hundreds of
11 volunteers, including 444 dentists and 98 dental labs;
12 Whereas, Since its inception in 1991, the DDS program has
13 provided comprehensive dental treatment to 6,141 Hoosiers
14 with seriously neglected dental problems; and
15 Whereas, This year, the DDS program donated $21.8
16 million in dental treatment to Hoosiers with disabilities or who
17 are elderly or medically fragile: Therefore,
18 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly
19 of the State of Indiana, the House of Representatives
20 concurring:
21 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly
22 recognizes the tremendous impact the Donated Dental Services
23 program has in Indiana.
2026 RC 1513/DI JR

2
1 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is directed to
2 transmit copies of this Resolution to the Indiana Dental
3 Association.
2026 RC 1513/DI JR

